# Add Registration, Separate Login, and Landing Page

## Background

Currently the app has only a **login** form (`Auth/create.blade.php`) — there is no way for new users to **sign up**. The root route (`/`) immediately redirects to the jobs listing. The user wants:

1. **Registration (Sign Up)** — a new page where users can create an account (name, email, password, confirm password).
2. **Login** — keep the existing login form, but link it to the new sign-up page and vice-versa.
3. **A beautiful landing page** at `/` — when visitors arrive they see a hero section showcasing the job board, with a CTA to browse jobs (`/jobs`).

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The landing page will become the new `/` home route. Authenticated users will still be able to navigate to `/jobs` via the navbar and the landing page CTA.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Registration will create a standard `User` record with `name`, `email`, and `password` — no email verification is added (matching the existing simple auth flow).

